result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan M Swadner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ryan M Swadner is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ryan M Swadner was found guilty of Homicide by Veh. Use-Control. Substance, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(am).
  • Ryan M Swadner was found guilty of Homicide by Veh. Use-Control. Substance, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(am).
  • Ryan M Swadner was found guilty of Homicide by Veh. Use-Control. Substance, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(am).
  • Ryan M Swadner was found guilty of Cause Injury/Operate-Control. Substance (1st) (PAC<0.15), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)3.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Ryan M Swadner in court with attorney Nila Robinson.  Greg Parker and Tara Jenswold appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Motion to adjourn argued by Attny Robinson and Attny  Jenswold in addition to their written motion and response.  Court makes a statement and denies the motion.  Matthew B., Tiffany A., and Wanda B. all address the Court.  Det. Chris G. is sworn and questioned by Attny Parker.  Exhibits #1, 2 & 3 are marked, identified, offered and received in to evidence.  Cross exam by Attny Robinson. Parties have reviewed the PSI with no factual errors.  Recess at 10:35, reconvene at 10:55 a.m.  Shannon B. sworn by the Court and questioned by Attny Robinson.  No cross.  DA Parker reads some case law.  Remarks for sentencing.  arguments by Attny Robinson.  Defendant makes a statement.  rebuttal by Attny Parker.  Objection - no action.  Citizenship, voting, and/or firearms information provided.  Court sentences defendant as follows:  Ct. 1 - 16 years (6 confinement +10 ES), $2500 fine+costs, DNA sample, 5 year revocation and IID.  Ct. 3 - 14 years ( 4 confinement + 10 ES) consecutive, same other conditions, Ct. 5 - 15 years (5 confinement + 10 ES) consecutive, same other conditions, Ct. 11 - 1 year jail, concurrent, $2,000 fine + costs, 2 year revocation and IID.  Extended Supervision conditions:  Absolute sobriety, No Class B except as authroized by Agent, AODA evaluation and followthrough, Handwritten apology letters to victim/family and no contact with them as noted in PSI unless waived in writing, Comply with any counseling recommended., DNA sample, Random UA's unless Agent determines otherwise, No illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription, full time work or 10 job search/week, 100 hours community service per year while on ES to include speeches about drugged driving.  Not eligible for ERP or CIP.  Defense requests any medications to be continued.  So ordered.  Appeal rights.  Credit for any time served.

3.  Court will allow operation of motor vehicle on private property with permission of the property owner and there are no passengers.  Property should not be open to the general public.
4.  Court will not remove the Class B establishment restriction regarding businesses whose primary purpose is to serve alcohol.
5.  Court will allow entry into restaurants with a bar as long as the defendant is seated only in the restaurant.  Defendant may pass through the bar area, but cannot be seated there, even if its waiting for restaurant seating.
